WEBVTT

00:07.490 --> 00:14.919
a new year, another turn of the calendar, another round of fireworks and resolutions.

00:14.939 --> 00:18.423
But before we rush into what's next, let's pause.

00:20.466 --> 00:35.123
Scripture says, teach us to number our days that we may gain a heart of wisdom, not to count the days gone by, but to make the days ahead count.

00:35.143 --> 00:37.266
Every sunrise is mercy renewed,

00:38.050 --> 00:41.714
Every breath is grace extended.

00:41.734 --> 00:47.279
And as the clock strikes midnight, we're reminded, time isn't ours to keep.

00:48.440 --> 00:49.781
It's God's to redeem.

00:52.224 --> 00:57.969
The Bible reminds us, if anyone is in Christ, they are a new creation.

00:58.910 --> 01:01.293
The old has gone.

01:01.493 --> 01:03.675
The new has come.

01:03.695 --> 01:06.898
So this year, let's not just turn a page.

01:07.650 --> 01:09.652
Let's turn our hearts.

01:09.672 --> 01:22.966
Let's walk into the unknown with fame, trusting the author who's already written every day.

01:22.986 --> 01:23.247
Morning.

01:24.588 --> 01:26.871
For those of you who don't know me, my name is Jonathan Conrad.

01:26.911 --> 01:31.355
I'm an elder here at Candy Perodes, and I have a privilege to speak with you this morning.

01:31.696 --> 01:33.057
So a question.

01:33.918 --> 01:35.460
Who in here likes coffee?

01:36.881 --> 01:37.202
Coffee.

01:37.222 --> 01:37.522
Good.

01:37.602 --> 01:39.524
Nobody's getting any yes, this is mine.

01:40.185 --> 01:46.331
So seriously, I want to, today we're going to be talking about a trip that my wife and I took down to Columbia.

01:46.371 --> 01:50.856
We were in Medellin, we were just went north of Medellin, and we visited a coffee plantation.

01:51.136 --> 01:55.861
And we met a guy named Miguel, and this I think you're going to see here, Miguel, this is Miguel.

01:55.901 --> 01:59.165
Miguel is the coolest guy, but we decided to go tour this coffee plantation.

01:59.185 --> 02:04.050
We were down there, I was actually down there on a work trip, and we thought we'd visit Hatillo coffee.

02:04.290 --> 02:05.291
That's this guy's coffee.

02:05.311 --> 02:18.804
And Miguel was a great guy, but one of the things that we went through, and as he was talking about the coffee process, the plantation, everything he did, why he's doing this, why he farms, why he cares about it, how they do it there.

02:18.824 --> 02:33.938
One of the thing that really hit me about his whole story was our big idea for the day, which is God's gifts are clearly visible, and they're shaping our lives actively, every day.

02:34.530 --> 02:36.814
The gifts that He's given you is shaping your life.

02:37.936 --> 02:40.120
But you gotta look at it, you gotta use it, right?

02:40.841 --> 02:45.569
So before we get to more, let's pray and then we'll dive in, okay?

02:45.590 --> 02:47.673
Father, we thank you so much for bringing us here this morning.

02:47.693 --> 02:52.181
We thank you for the chance to celebrate the birth of your son Jesus and what that means for us.

02:52.582 --> 02:59.474
Well, we thank you for bringing gifts into our lives, helping us to be passionate for you to work for your glory.

02:59.554 --> 03:05.461
Well, I pray that you be with this morning as we study your word, we study what it is you have for us to do in our lives.

03:05.481 --> 03:07.263
We lift this to you in Jesus' name, amen.

03:08.424 --> 03:20.118
So I go to tour of Miguel's plantation and the coolest part about this is we get there and you'll see some photos here of when we walked up, right?

03:20.138 --> 03:21.559
We walk up and this is the plantation.

03:21.579 --> 03:22.881
We drove up north into the mountains.

03:23.221 --> 03:25.844
We get into this beautiful landscape.

03:25.904 --> 03:27.506
It is incredibly beautiful there.

03:27.586 --> 03:32.253
We, we walk up to his, this is one of the outbuildings that he does a lot of the processing of a coffee.

03:32.915 --> 03:37.963
And Miguel comes up and he's, by the way, this is going to come back, but he carries that tree with him throughout this tour.

03:38.283 --> 03:39.365
That's one of the coffee plants.

03:39.665 --> 03:44.974
But the first thing we do is we walk up, um, and I'm thinking, I, you guys have probably done plenty of tours.

03:44.994 --> 03:47.558
You walk up, you're thinking, okay, we're going to get on some tram, some bus.

03:47.578 --> 03:48.780
He's going to take us out to the field.

03:48.800 --> 03:49.822
He's going to show us the plants.

03:49.862 --> 03:51.885
We're going to end up in a gift shop where I'm supposed to buy coffee.

03:52.526 --> 03:53.427
This is how that's going to go.

03:54.309 --> 03:55.090
But it didn't at all.

03:55.906 --> 04:00.553
The cool, Miguel, we walk up, and the first thing he says is the question I started with.

04:00.573 --> 04:01.234
Do you like coffee?

04:02.316 --> 04:03.738
And I said, yeah, I love coffee.

04:03.778 --> 04:05.060
Kelly, not so much, my wife.

04:05.480 --> 04:06.662
But I love coffee.

04:06.682 --> 04:07.543
And he's like, great.

04:07.563 --> 04:08.805
And he says, what kind of coffee do you like?

04:08.845 --> 04:09.927
And I said, well, not Starbucks.

04:09.947 --> 04:10.908
And he goes, thank you.

04:11.489 --> 04:11.930
Thank you.

04:12.531 --> 04:13.292
And I said, yeah.

04:13.312 --> 04:15.195
And he goes, yeah, that's terrible coffee.

04:15.255 --> 04:17.238
He said, do you like artisanal coffee?

04:17.258 --> 04:18.319
That's what we make.

04:18.339 --> 04:19.641
And I was like, oh, cool.

04:19.962 --> 04:23.607
But he said, well, before we go anywhere, he said, can we just sit?

04:23.687 --> 04:25.490
And he pulls us up to his porch.

04:25.954 --> 04:27.737
And he says, can we just sit and talk for a minute?

04:28.938 --> 04:31.502
And I'm thinking, it's okay, you know.

04:31.843 --> 04:35.007
So he pulls up some lawn chairs on his porch and he adds this little set up here.

04:35.027 --> 04:37.411
You can see he's got like a little Mr. Coffee making his coffee.

04:38.212 --> 04:46.845
And he's sitting there and he says, I just want to, I think it's the right thing to do is just start with, with why I do this, like why I care about coffee.

04:47.806 --> 04:48.948
And I thought, what a cool thing to do.

04:49.629 --> 04:52.072
So we sit down and he tells us his story.

04:52.473 --> 04:53.234
And he says,

04:53.890 --> 04:56.074
He says, you know, I grew up on this farm.

04:56.134 --> 04:57.756
I grew up farming with my dad.

04:57.937 --> 04:59.199
My dad loves coffee.

04:59.239 --> 05:02.324
He's always done it, but he's never been able to make it successful.

05:02.524 --> 05:03.766
He's never been able to do much with it.

05:04.608 --> 05:05.790
But he's like, but we love it.

05:06.030 --> 05:07.993
He loves what it means for his family.

05:08.013 --> 05:09.676
He loves what it means for his country.

05:09.696 --> 05:11.439
It's one of their major exports, of course.

05:11.479 --> 05:12.801
Everybody knows Colombian coffee.

05:13.202 --> 05:15.025
So he just, it was a passion of his.

05:15.065 --> 05:18.530
He grew up loving coffee and what it meant for everything around him.

05:19.692 --> 05:20.754
But as he got older,

05:21.186 --> 05:23.730
He just, you know, it's not working in terms of making money.

05:23.770 --> 05:25.632
There's not much he can do with his life with this.

05:25.652 --> 05:28.436
He feels like it's just, you know, I love it, but what can I do with it?

05:29.097 --> 05:37.650
Also, he gets a little disenfranchised because the bigger companies are coming in at this point and they're buying up all the small farms and you can't compete with the big guys.

05:37.710 --> 05:42.637
And it's just, you know, he's frustrated and his dad is, he's mad because his, you know, his dad is working so hard and can't do much.

05:43.698 --> 05:45.441
So he says, I don't think this is for me.

05:46.242 --> 05:48.946
So despite how much I love it, I've got to do something else.

05:49.858 --> 05:54.965
So he goes and gets a degree in engineering and decides to just go a whole different path.

05:54.985 --> 05:57.909
And he actually gets a job with a company, a global company in Europe.

05:58.510 --> 06:00.252
And he's an engineer over in Europe for many years.

06:00.753 --> 06:01.614
And he does pretty well.

06:02.335 --> 06:04.759
But then one day he realizes he hates engineering.

06:06.201 --> 06:07.242
Sorry for any engineers in here.

06:07.282 --> 06:10.426
But he said it's the most boring thing in the world, which I happen to agree with him.

06:11.588 --> 06:13.130
But he's like, this is terrible.

06:13.631 --> 06:14.392
This is not for me.

06:14.432 --> 06:15.413
The passion wasn't there.

06:15.674 --> 06:18.898
But he learned some incredible skill that he could apply.

06:19.554 --> 06:20.756
And he's like, I got an idea.

06:21.397 --> 06:22.519
So he calls his dad.

06:22.539 --> 06:25.584
And his dad at this point is getting older and kind of ailing.

06:25.624 --> 06:27.026
And he says, I want to take over the farm.

06:27.687 --> 06:28.308
I'm going to come back.

06:28.729 --> 06:29.450
And I want to take over the farm.

06:29.470 --> 06:30.191
And I've got an idea.

06:30.692 --> 06:33.877
I want to turn this into a co-op.

06:33.897 --> 06:36.462
I want to co-op with all the other farmers that are local here.

06:36.922 --> 06:38.104
And I want us to work together.

06:38.224 --> 06:39.406
And I will distribute.

06:39.827 --> 06:42.892
Our Hatio coffee will be the distributor of all the farms.

06:43.573 --> 06:44.455
And we'll work together.

06:44.495 --> 06:46.578
That way we can all survive.

06:46.786 --> 06:49.250
We can increase the quality, which is his big focus.

06:49.290 --> 06:55.760
And he's taking this engineering skill and creates incredible processes around how do we make the best possible quality coffee.

06:56.662 --> 06:57.904
And he's focused on that now.

06:57.944 --> 07:00.268
So he's, he's combining that passion and that skill.

07:00.588 --> 07:04.995
And it's this cool story I'm seeing unfold as he's talking about it.

07:05.015 --> 07:07.339
And then he, he says, you know, so I came back, I started this.

07:07.359 --> 07:11.666
We have a co-op now, the coffee that you're going to get might come from any of the given farms.

07:12.098 --> 07:40.274
And and also now we can employ all the locals who don't have any other things to do in this in this region He can employ them give them jobs so they tend his farm So I was just thinking this is such an incredible thing and it hit me the biggest thing that hit me about his is that God gives us with passion and purpose He gives us passion and purpose Miguel loves coffee

07:40.514 --> 07:46.502
And what it means for his family, like I said, his country, all that stuff, he wants it to be the best, he wants it to be the best for everybody.

07:46.582 --> 07:49.907
And then he's also thinking, and I can make people's lives better.

07:50.528 --> 07:51.709
I can help the other farmers.

07:51.869 --> 07:53.992
I can take this passion and turn it into something bigger.

07:56.115 --> 08:07.090
So Ephesians 2 10 says, for we are God's handiwork created in Christ Jesus to do good works, which God prepared in advance for us to do, you have a gift.

08:09.122 --> 08:11.425
So many people say, I don't not really get it anything.

08:11.805 --> 08:12.606
Yes, you are.

08:14.248 --> 08:14.909
Yes, you are.

08:15.790 --> 08:17.352
God has gifted you with something.

08:17.473 --> 08:18.654
He's gifted you with a passion.

08:18.954 --> 08:20.977
Maybe you think, well, it's not really something I can do.

08:21.518 --> 08:24.141
Miguel didn't think it was either, not at first.

08:25.583 --> 08:27.705
But God has given him that passion and he didn't let it go.

08:29.007 --> 08:35.155
He kept, even though Miguel moved literally a part of the global way, that ember was still there of that passion.

08:35.195 --> 08:36.076
I want to do coffee.

08:36.837 --> 08:37.618
I want to do this.

08:37.794 --> 08:45.907
So, there's another verse here, I wanted to read Matthew 5, 16, in the same way, let your light shine before others that they may see your good deeds and glorify your Father in heaven.

08:46.227 --> 08:49.072
He took what he was gifted with and he's helping others.

08:50.834 --> 08:58.086
So, I want to ask you, what is the passion that, when I mention this, what are you thinking about?

08:59.167 --> 09:04.456
What is that thing in your heart that if somebody mentions it, you're like, can we pull up a chair and talk?

09:04.476 --> 09:05.938
I got to tell you about this.

09:07.138 --> 09:08.540
That's what God has given you.

09:08.560 --> 09:09.081
That's it.

09:09.101 --> 09:09.482
That's it.

09:09.622 --> 09:10.343
That's the passion.

09:12.567 --> 09:13.889
Grab hold of it and don't let it go.

09:14.530 --> 09:15.732
We're going into a new year here.

09:15.772 --> 09:20.640
Everybody talks about we were just talking about what that's going to mean for you and where you're going to use it and how you're going to what you're going to do this year.

09:21.441 --> 09:26.629
Make it the year that you take God's passion and turn it into something that you work for God's Kingdom.

09:28.272 --> 09:32.018
So, so then we go to

09:32.162 --> 09:32.683
the fields.

09:32.883 --> 09:34.745
We go out, he says, okay, now we can go out into the fields.

09:34.885 --> 09:44.357
So we go out into the fields and you'll see he shows us more of the trees and we walk out and we actually see the, we see the trees themselves.

09:44.397 --> 09:45.659
He shows us his whole process.

09:45.699 --> 09:47.381
Now he's getting, now he's geeking out over this stuff.

09:47.401 --> 09:48.002
He's really excited.

09:48.042 --> 09:50.245
He's out in the field and he's like, okay, this is how we plant.

09:50.265 --> 09:51.186
This is what it looks like.

09:51.346 --> 09:52.227
It's beautiful areas.

09:52.548 --> 09:53.509
He has the trees.

09:53.549 --> 09:54.290
He shows us

09:54.498 --> 09:58.123
How to pick those cherries by the way, I didn't even realize that coffee was a cherry.

09:58.143 --> 10:21.074
It's a fruit I didn't know that but it's a fruit It's a cherry and he and there was a point where he squeezed the cherry into my hand and it's this This it's covered in juice and fruit and he says just put in your mouth and taste the taste of fruit and it's really sweet and he says yeah And he's telling me it's like yeah, that's because the ones we plant on this hill are sweeter now I'm gonna go to the other hill and then you'll taste it's less sweet It's different and he's he knows exactly what soil produces what and

10:21.346 --> 10:22.749
He knows where they're going to plant the trees.

10:22.769 --> 10:25.816
He knows which trees he wants to take the new seeds from to plant the other trees.

10:26.216 --> 10:31.688
So all these things he's doing, and he's showing us how this works, and he's just really, really excited about the whole process.

10:32.450 --> 10:41.970
And again, I'm seeing that passion start to combine with this skill that he has that he's developed for the process, the quality control, all these things that he's doing.

10:42.146 --> 10:43.868
So then you can go to the next slide here.

10:43.888 --> 10:47.392
You'll see this is the coffee bean he put into my hand and he said, no, taste that.

10:47.433 --> 10:47.893
And I did.

10:47.973 --> 10:53.620
And you see the plantation here, all the plants, this plant on the bottom right is just overwhelmed with fruit.

10:53.720 --> 10:56.544
And he's like, that's the tree I'm taking from next because it's awesome.

10:56.784 --> 10:57.745
It's going to produce more fruit.

10:58.226 --> 10:59.347
So he's going through this thing.

11:00.268 --> 11:11.282
And then I just, again, this clicked for me that I thought it was so amazing that God's gifts to us, he gives us skill and determination to excel for his glory.

11:12.546 --> 11:15.530
If you are passionate about what we just talked about, there's a passion for you.

11:16.552 --> 11:18.915
You wanna do it well, right?

11:19.837 --> 11:20.578
You wanna do it well.

11:21.179 --> 11:25.445
So if God gives you that passion, next is go and develop that skill.

11:26.827 --> 11:30.973
Because he has given this to you, because he wants you to combine the two.

11:30.993 --> 11:36.621
And again, I'm gonna go back to what I thought was so cool in seeing this story, is that Miguel didn't think he had it.

11:36.662 --> 11:38.224
He's like, this is not gonna work.

11:39.486 --> 11:42.450
But then he goes away and God says, well, because you're not done yet.

11:42.530 --> 11:42.770
Right?

11:43.071 --> 11:43.932
I gave you the passion.

11:44.593 --> 11:45.354
Now you need the skill.

11:46.135 --> 11:51.803
So he sends him, you know, in his life, you can see God's fingerprints on this, where he goes and learns this skill.

11:52.845 --> 11:54.567
And then he's like, I know how to apply.

11:54.587 --> 11:56.830
I know what I can do for the coffee, for the business.

11:57.471 --> 11:58.492
Now I can do this.

11:58.513 --> 11:59.294
I can make it better.

11:59.854 --> 12:01.457
So then he goes back and he applies the two.

12:01.797 --> 12:03.059
And now something's going.

12:03.419 --> 12:05.542
Now Hatillo Coffee is here.

12:06.203 --> 12:07.225
And he's doing great things.

12:07.245 --> 12:10.009
And he's employing people and giving jobs and doing all this amazing stuff.

12:10.029 --> 12:10.930
Is that not cool?

12:12.546 --> 12:16.710
And it was like, how amazing is God to do this in his life?

12:17.211 --> 12:24.338
You know, 2 Timothy says, for this reason I remind you to fan into flame the gift of God, which is in you through the laying on of my hands.

12:25.879 --> 12:32.125
And Colossians 3 says, whatever you do, work at it with all your heart as if working for the Lord, not for human masters.

12:33.106 --> 12:33.707
That's Miguel.

12:34.668 --> 12:39.833
He is working, the coffee is his life, but also he's able to change others' lives.

12:40.473 --> 12:41.234
And he's doing this.

12:41.570 --> 12:44.514
and impacting others, and that's just such a cool story to see.

12:44.874 --> 12:46.236
So I'm gonna ask you this.

12:47.417 --> 12:53.484
What do you need to do to fan into flame that passion?

12:55.607 --> 13:01.474
Maybe you need to do, sorry, you probably won't go to Europe to learn something new, sorry.

13:01.915 --> 13:03.056
If you do, cool, do it.

13:04.257 --> 13:06.180
It's not necessarily that big of a thing, right?

13:06.300 --> 13:08.082
Maybe you just need to ask somebody to mentor you.

13:09.026 --> 13:11.528
Maybe you just need to say, I want to volunteer.

13:11.548 --> 13:12.589
I want to learn on the job.

13:12.609 --> 13:13.410
I want to see how it works.

13:15.913 --> 13:16.633
Take the step.

13:17.734 --> 13:19.196
God has given you that passion for a reason.

13:19.216 --> 13:20.757
And if you're stuck and you're like, I don't know how to apply it.

13:20.777 --> 13:21.698
I don't know what to do with it.

13:23.160 --> 13:24.781
Take the step to develop the skill.

13:25.902 --> 13:27.564
And also never give up on the passion.

13:27.824 --> 13:29.085
You may think it's not going to work.

13:29.386 --> 13:30.507
It's not going to work now.

13:30.907 --> 13:31.788
Maybe God's not done.

13:32.949 --> 13:34.971
Maybe God hasn't taught you the next step.

13:35.852 --> 13:37.874
Don't give up on that passion, right?

13:39.426 --> 13:43.812
So this was a funny part because at this point, Miguel, we're out there and he's all giddy.

13:43.832 --> 13:46.075
He's so excited about this whole plantation.

13:46.115 --> 13:50.181
And he comes up to me and he says, he's like, OK, do you want to know my problems?

13:51.883 --> 13:54.106
And I was like, do we need to go back to the porch and sit down again?

13:54.147 --> 13:56.810
Like, I've got plenty of my own, Miguel.

13:57.191 --> 13:57.732
We could share.

13:59.234 --> 14:02.398
But he was like, well, I think it's important that you know my challenges.

14:03.560 --> 14:08.146
And I was like, OK. And I was thinking he was going to say, like, distribution, whatever quality control.

14:08.322 --> 14:08.642
He didn't.

14:08.702 --> 14:09.623
He goes, come here.

14:10.344 --> 14:11.685
And he walks me over to a tree.

14:12.266 --> 14:14.187
And the tree has this on it.

14:14.428 --> 14:16.530
It's discolored.

14:17.150 --> 14:19.793
And he says, this is coffee rust.

14:21.214 --> 14:23.076
And I was like, ah, what is it?

14:23.516 --> 14:26.079
And he said, well, this tree, I said, what does it do to it?

14:26.099 --> 14:28.761
And he said, well, it just hinders production.

14:28.881 --> 14:29.922
It'll slow down.

14:30.002 --> 14:31.203
It won't produce as much fruit.

14:31.624 --> 14:34.066
And if you don't do something about it, eventually it'll stop producing altogether.

14:35.147 --> 14:36.388
And I said, man, does it spread a lot?

14:36.408 --> 14:38.290
And he said, well, we can treat it with

14:38.754 --> 14:40.596
fungicides and things like that.

14:40.636 --> 14:42.258
We can see it so we can treat it.

14:42.298 --> 14:45.122
And he said, but the tree is really, it's going to slow its production.

14:45.142 --> 14:45.743
It's not going to be as good.

14:45.763 --> 14:48.726
We can't really plant from it again, that kind of thing.

14:48.746 --> 14:50.268
So he's like, we've got to be really careful about it.

14:50.308 --> 14:51.630
We're watching it all the time.

14:52.171 --> 14:55.255
And he said, so come here and I'll show you the second one.

14:55.635 --> 14:56.837
And he walks me over to the second one.

14:57.738 --> 14:58.579
And it's these things.

14:58.619 --> 15:02.564
He picks a cherry, and he walks it over to me, and he says this right here.

15:02.984 --> 15:07.570
And it looks just like the regular chairs, except there's a

15:08.066 --> 15:10.730
pin-prick hole on the bottom of it.

15:11.991 --> 15:14.455
And then he squeezed it in my hand like he did the other fruit.

15:14.955 --> 15:24.568
And instead of it being juicy and the fruit coming out, he squeezed it in my hand and it's dust and brown and rubriddle.

15:25.710 --> 15:28.874
And there's these tiny little beetles all over it.

15:29.735 --> 15:31.878
And he says, that's the coffee borer beetle.

15:32.840 --> 15:37.586
And he said, they bore into this cherry and they eat it from within.

15:38.402 --> 15:41.166
and they spread all over it at different trees.

15:41.928 --> 15:44.872
So before I go on, I want to ask you, which one do you think is more dangerous?

15:48.578 --> 15:48.859
Anybody?

